          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a manual used by priests and outlining the rules and regulations (Hindu laws, Dharma) governing the summoning and installation of deities into a physical support, especially in the context of architecture such as discussion of diagrams for the foundation of a building (vāstumaṇḍala).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Pratiṣṭhāpaddhati</title>
              <title type="vernacular">प्रतिष्ठापद्धति</title>
              <author>
                <persName type="authority">Trivikrama</persName>
              </author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīraghusūrisūnutrivikramasūriviracitāyāṃ pratiṣṭāpaddhatau tu parigrahaḥ // śubham astusarvajagato giriśaprasādāt // (f. 7v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
